# E-Commerce ERD Design Assignment

## Overview
This project contains an Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD) designed for an e-commerce database system.

The ERD models the relationships between customers, orders, products, payments, deliveries, suppliers, and categories within a structured relational database environment.

## Objectives
The purpose of this assignment was to:
- Design a relational database structure
- Apply database normalization principles
- Define primary and foreign keys
- Create relationships between entities
- Model a real-world e-commerce system

## Entities Included
- CUSTOMER
- ADDRESS
- ORDERS
- ORDER_ITEM
- PRODUCT
- CATEGORY
- SUPPLIER
- PAYMENT
- DELIVERY

## Key Features
- Customer order management
- Product and category relationships
- Supplier management
- Payment tracking
- Delivery tracking
- Proper primary and foreign key relationships

## Relationships Implemented
- One customer can place many orders
- One customer can have multiple addresses
- One order can contain multiple order items
- Products can appear in multiple order items
- One category can contain multiple products
- One supplier can supply multiple products
- One order can have multiple payments
- One order can have multiple deliveries

